  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "For example, Gao et al. [32] introduced a neural network architecture with features resembling a recurrent neural network.",
    "This model achieved high accuracy by sequentially predicting catalysts, solvents, reagents, and temperatures, taking into account their interdependence across a broad spectrum of organic reactions.",
    "Maser et al. [33] focused on elucidating the roles of different species involved in reactions, such as metals, ligands, bases, solvents, and additives.",
    "They tackled the prediction of reaction conditions by developing multi-label classification models specifically tailored for Suzuki, Negishi, C-N couplings, and Pauson-Khand reactions.",
    "Recently, Kwon et al. [34] pointed out that previous techniques provided only a single prediction per reaction, lacking a comprehensive list of possible reaction conditions."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "For example, Gao et al. [32] introduced a neural network architecture with features resembling a recurrent neural network.",
    "Maser et al. [33] focused on elucidating the roles of different species involved in reactions, such as metals, ligands, bases, solvents, and additives.",
    "Recently, Kwon et al. [34] pointed out that previous techniques provided only a single prediction per reaction, lacking a comprehensive list of possible reaction conditions."
  ]
